  "texts": [
    "(1) First, the various evaluation metrics used to assess the performance of the M-DQN model in the Bitcoin trading task are discussed in terms of PnL and risk-adjusted level.",
    "(2) Second, the M-DQN model's performance is analyzed under different risk levels.",
    "By varying the risk thresholds in the reward function, the most suitable risk level for the trading strategy is identified.",
    "The impact of varying the number of active trades on the M-DQN model performance is also assessed, with the goal of determining the optimal active trading threshold for the trading strategy.",
    "(3) Third, the efficiency of the proposed reward function is compared with two existing reward functions from the literature, to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach."
  ],
